<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Pre-prove</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Ubuntu:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,700;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,700&display=swap');

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
      font-family: "Ubuntu";
    }

    body {
      height: 100vh;
      width: 100vw;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      background-color: #253752;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 16px;
    }

    input {
      border-radius: 4px;
      display: block;
      padding: 8px;
      min-width: 350px;
      margin: 16px 0;
    }

    button {
      min-width: 100px;
      border: 0;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      background-color: #256ad1;
      color: #fff;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    body>* {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    body>h2{
      font-size: 48px;
    }

    .not-ready {
      background-color: #fc0000;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 24px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <h1>
    You are about to answer 10 simple questions that would prove you are indeed a web developer. You have <b>1</b>m
    <b>10</b>s
    to answer them. If you score lower than average you will not be able to take the survey. It will be assumed you
    are not a web developer
  </h1>

  <form action="/prove-lobby" method="post">
    <input type="hidden" name="directive" value="take test">
    <button type="submit">Take Test</button>
  </form>

  <form action="/prove-lobby" method="post">
    <input type="hidden" name="directive" value="Not Ready">
    <button type="submit" class="not-ready">Not Ready</button>
  </form>
</body>

</html>